<item>
            <title>[MAHOUT-882] TopItems.getTopUsers ignores rescoring</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/MAHOUT-882</link>
                <project id="12310751" key="MAHOUT">Mahout</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;I believe TopUsers.getTopUsers() is not properly handling the rescoredSimilarity:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
TopItems.getTopUsers:
&lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;double&lt;/span&gt; rescoredSimilarity = rescorer == &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;null&lt;/span&gt; ? similarity : rescorer.rescore(userID, similarity);
      &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;if&lt;/span&gt; (!&lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;Double&lt;/span&gt;.isNaN(rescoredSimilarity) &amp;amp;&amp;amp; (!full || rescoredSimilarity &amp;gt; lowestTopValue)) {
        topUsers.add(&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;new&lt;/span&gt; SimilarUser(userID, similarity));
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;It is checking rescoredSimilarity for everything, but then not passing it in like getTopItems does.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
